<br>
A little bit of each is best for slash, since you've got both reactionary styles, but neither is all that great.<br>
<br>
Also, mathematically on paper, it's better to take 1 rank of MoPain then 1 rank of Dualist's Reflexes than it is to take 2 ranks of either.  MoPain is *always* more effective at each level than DR in buffing damage.  But, not so much better that it's more cost effective to spend 3 points on MoPain II before spending 1 point on DR 1. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tklausing>tklausing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Professional Board Spammer</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#000000>(12/9/02 8:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://tklausing.home.attbi.com/image/disco.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realm Abilities</span><hr size=1> Either way, I'd focus more on Evade because:<br>
